<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1087969-i-am-in-love-with-the-language-in-true">I am in love with the language in True Grit, it is hilarious and poetic at the same time. What other books use the same device so effectively, specifically to the Old American West, and the florid speech of the late 1800s (excluding Mark Twain, of course, the father of it all)? I thought at one time that Little Big Man may fall under that category, but I can&#39;t locate my copy. Any suggestions or recommendations?</a>
