<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/75860511-carissa"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_100x100-259587f1619f5253426a4fa6fb508831.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/75860511-carissa">Carissa</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">For an 8 year old, I would agree to wait a few years. There is some language such as &quot;h*ll,&quot; &quot;d*mn,&quot; and &quot;son of a b****,&quot; but each of these are used <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">For an 8 year old, I would agree to wait a few years. There is some language such as "h*ll," "d*mn," and "son of a b****," but each of these are used only once or twice throughout the book. <br /><br />Also, it may be considered fairly dark since the main character is a 14 year old girl on a mission to avenge her father by killing his murderer, and there are references to dead bodies, hanging, and blood from wounds. <br /><br />My personal recommendation for reading this book would be age 12+, but I always prefer telling the "red flags" parents may be concerned about, so they can make their own decision. I hope this helps!<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
