  <span id="freeText4780676393807385754" style="display:none"><b> People do not give it credence that a fourteen-year-old girl could leave home and go off in the wintertime to avenge her father's blood but it did not seem so strange then, although I will say it did not happen every day.</b><br /><br />It's October and I usually read horror related books during the entire month but I had to make an exception with this one. Wow, just wow what a masterpiece! Not only is this one of the best Western books I've read but it's one of the best books I've ever read. I simply couldn't put it down. I'm familiar with both films, the John Wayne classic and the Coen brothers version and while they are well done movies, neither one of them compares to the book in my opinion. I cannot believe that this novel was out of print for a while but got released again due to the popularity of the 2010 movie. For those of you not familiar with the story it's about a young girl named Mattie Ross whose father gets murdered by a man he took in during his time of need named Tom Chaney. Tom is on the run and the law doesn't seem to mind, but Mattie Ross takes it upon herself to find him and bring him to justice but she can't do it alone. She finds the meanest U.S<br /> Marshal, Rooster Cogburn,(who has true grit)to go along to her trip to find Chaney and it's an unforgettable journey. I can't recommend this book enough. My copy had an afterword from Donna Tartt with her saying it's one her favorite books of all time and it makes me adore her even more. 5 Colt. forty-fives out of 5.</span>
